data.enText: great respect and admiration; a good opinion of sb
She is held in high esteem by her colleagues.

data.chText: 小小礼物，聊表敬意，请笑纳。
data.enText: Please accept this small gift as a token of our esteem.
not used in the progressive tenses
to respect and admire sb/sth very much

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: to think of sb/sth in a particular way

data.chText: 她被认为是最完美的小说家。
data.enText: She was esteemed the perfect novelist.

ex.chText: 她的善良赢得了邻居的尊敬。
ex.enText: Her kindness has earned the respect of her neighbours.

ex.chText: 他的同事非常钦佩他的工作能力。
ex.enText: All his colleagues have the greatest respect for his work.

synonyms.bx: 指对他人的品质、学识或技艺的钦佩。

ex.chText: 那位年轻人用爱慕的眼神注视着她。
ex.enText: The young man gazed at her in admiration.

ex.chText: 他全家人对救援人员满怀敬佩之情。
ex.enText: His whole family was full of admiration for the rescuers.

ex.chText: 读者都对这位作家十分敬重。
ex.enText: The readers held this writer in great esteem.

ex.chText: 公众对教师的尊重程度有所下降。
ex.enText: There has been a drop in public esteem for teachers.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，含赞赏、仰慕之意。

ex.chText: 对所有队员而言，赢得这场比赛事关国家荣誉。
ex.enText: For all the players, winning this game is a matter of national honour.

ex.chText: 为了捍卫家族的荣誉，他决定迎接挑战。
ex.enText: He decided to meet the challenge in order to defend the honour of his family.

synonyms.bx: 指别人对自己、自己的国家、家庭等表现出的敬意，含令人引以为荣之意。

tr: an attitude of admiration or esteem
example: she lost all respect for him

tr: a feeling of delighted approval and liking
the condition of being honored (esteemed or respected or well regarded)
example: a man who has earned high regard
she looked on this affair as a joke
He thinks of himself as a brilliant musician
He is reputed to be intelligent

value.def: Esteem is the admiration and respect that you feel towards another person.

example.ex: He is held in high esteem by colleagues in the construction industry...
example.tran: 建筑业的同行们都非常敬重他。

example.ex: Their public esteem has never been lower...
example.tran: 他们在公众中的信誉从未如此之低。

example.ex: He said he retained immense regard and esteem for the prime minister.
example.tran: 他说他一直极其尊重和敬仰首相。

value.def: If you esteem someone or something, you respect or admire them.

example.ex: I greatly esteem your message in the midst of our hard struggle.
example.tran: 您在我们奋力抗争时发来的电文让我充满了敬意。
